FT  11 MAY 91 / Appointments: Senior posts at HTV Group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HTV GROUP has made changes in its senior management. Mr Huw Davies ceases to
be chief executive of HTV Cymru/Wales to concentrate on his duties as group
director of television. Mr Emyr Daniel has been appointed managing director
of HTV Cymru/Wales, and to the group board. He continues as director of
programmes for HTV Cymru/Wales. Mr Ted George, a main board director,
succeeds Mr Ron Evans on his retirement as managing director of HTV West. Mr
Steve Matthews becomes director of programmes, HTV West, when Mr Derek Clark
retires next year. Mr John Elfed Jones has been appointed group deputy
chairman. He is chairman of Welsh Water, and will succeed Mr Idwal Symonds
when he retires as chairman of HTV Cymru/Wales at the end of next year.
Joining the board of HTV Cymru/Wales is Professor Lord Griffiths of
Fforestfach, chairman of the Centre of Policy Studies. Mr Colin Atkinson and
Mr Symonds have resigned as joint vice-chairman of the group but remain as
directors.
*****
