FT  11 MAY 91 / Letter: Encouraging the private investor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From A PORTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Mr Douglas Dale (Letters, May 8) suggests short term penal capital
gains tax will encourage long term investment. Many companies have found the
best long term shareholders are private individuals.
May I suggest a better answer would be to encourage the private investor by
equalising the tax treatment on direct and indirect investment. If
capitalism is to work we must have a tax system that penalises us if we
delegate our responsibilities to institutions not prepared to accept them.
A Porter,
The Pines,
19 Chantry Rise,
Penarth,
South Glamorgan
