<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 91 / Markets (At a glance): Two new unit trusts from Prolific
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Prolific, the fund management group, is launching two unit trusts in an
effort to take advantage of the improving conditions in the UK economy. The
Prolific recovery unit trust will aim for capital growth by investing in a
spread of relatively risky shares that have potentially high rewards. The
Prolific UK blue chip unit trust will aim for an above average total return
of capital and income, by investing mainly in companies that are part of the
FTSE 100 index. Much of the balance of the portfolio will be invested in the
second hundred largest companies. The trusts require a minimum investment of
Pounds 500 and will be launched on May 25.
</TEXT>
