<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 91 / Markets (At a glance): Templeton Int launches umbrella fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Templeton International has launched an umbrella fund, based in Luxembourg,
called Global Strategy. Investors will have a choice between 14 sub-funds,
denominated in US dollars, Deutschemarks and Swiss francs. The minimum
initial investment is Dollars 5,000, and further investments should be at
least Dollars 1,000.
The initial charge is 5.75 per cent for equity funds and between 1 and 4 per
cent for bond funds, with a switching charge of 1 per cent. The annual
management charge on the funds vary between 0.8 per cent and 2 per cent.
