<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 91 / Markets (At a glance): Political pointers from the 'misery
index'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Political pundits in the City, trying to guess the date of the next general
election, are examining the 'misery index' which adds the current rate of
inflation to the rate of unemployment. The idea is that the lower the level
of 'misery', the higher the government's chances of winning reelection will
be. It peaked just before Margaret Thatcher's resignation, and is showing
slight signs of going down, but analysts are hedging their bets on the
election date. JA
