<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 91 / The Lex Column: Gaming
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The excitements at Granada should not obscure another aspect of yesterday's
announcements: Bass's relentless pursuit of market leadership in all its
businesses. Yesterday it bought its way to the top spot in a bingo duopoly,
and abandoned a trailing position in bookmaking. The decision to sell the
Coral Racing betting shops leaves open the possibility of a duopoly there,
too, if some outsider picks them up and winkles the William Hill chain away
from Brent Walker, where they are none-too-securely perched. The mass-market
gaming business is starting to look enjoyably cosy - from the participants'
side of the fence, at least.
