<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 91 / Battle over Nissan car sales moves to court
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE, Motor Industry Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NISSAN UK, the privately owned distributor of Nissan vehicles in Britain,
will seek an injunction on Monday to stop Nissan Motor of Japan from
terminating its exclusive distribution agreement.
The long-running public battle between Nissan UK (NUK) and Nissan Motor
moves to the High Court for the first time on Monday with Nissan UK also
seeking substantial damages from the Japanese car maker.
It is seeking a court order to prevent Nissan Motor from selling its
vehicles in the UK to any company other than NUK. At the end of March Nissan
Motor announced that it had established a new company, Nissan Motor (GB), to
distribute all Nissan products in the UK from January 1 1992.
If Nissan UK gains the injunction, Nissan Motor will be prevented from
selling its vehicles to this new wholly owned subsidiary, which plans to run
a new dealer network replacing Nissan UK's 380-strong chain.
Nissan Motor wants the dispute to be arbitrated in Japan.
</TEXT>
