<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 91 / Associate of Milken indicted
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Alan Rosenthal, a key business associate of Mr Michael Milken and a
former head of the Beverly Hills-based convertible bond department of Drexel
Burham Lambert, has been indicted by a federal grand jury on a variety of
charges, including conspiracy, mail and securities fraud, embezzlement and
providing an illegal guarantee.
The indictment alleges that Mr Rosenthal conspired with Mr Milken, the
former Drexel 'junk bond king', and others, to confer unlawful economic
benefits on a former Drexel client, Mr David Solomon, and to misappropriate
funds from Solomon's clients. It also claims that one of Mr Rosenthal's
con-conspirators was Mr Solomon himself, who ran a high-yield money
management firm, Solomon Asset Management.
If found guilty on all charges, Mr Rosenthal could face a prison sentence of
51 years or Dollars 2.3m in fines. Mr Milken is already serving a prison
sentence after pleading guilty to securities law violations.
</TEXT>
