<TEXT>
AN INTRIGUING group of shareholders is being assembled at Pathfinders Group,
the USM-quoted entertainment and media recruitment agency which has been
chaired since last September by Mr Stephen Hargrave.
Mr Jon Pither, the former Amari Group chief executive and Glynwed
International director, has bought a 6.3 per cent stake and joined the
board. This follows the acquisition of a 3 per cent interest by Mr John
