FT  10 MAY 91 / Observer: Talking point
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A new party game in Ireland is suggesting venues that might break the
deadlock on the second strand of the talks on north-south relations. The
Irish government wants them to be held somewhere in Ireland itself.
Unionists, against travelling to the south while the 'foreign' government
has a constitutional claim over the north, want the Dublin government to
cross to their capital - London.
More serious compromises dreamed up so far include the Isle of Man. More
imaginative are a video conference so neither side need leave home ground,
and a circling aircraft.
My pick is a hot air balloon.
