FT  10 MAY 91 / Parliament and Politics: Reform of NHS back on political
centre stage - Health
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IVO DAWNAY, Political Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ANGRY exchanges between the prime minister and Mr Neil Kinnock at Commons
question time yesterday brought the government's National Health Service
reforms back to centre stage.
Claiming to have evidence that queue jumping was 'the order of the day', the
Labour leader repeatedly challenged Mr John Major to admit that 'the
clinical needs of patients are coming second to commercial considerations.'
To back his charges, Mr Kinnock quoted from a letter by Dr Kenneth Grant,
district general manager for the City and Hackney Health Authority, to
clinical directors at Bart's hospital on general practitioner fund holders
