Mr Ray Rowden, whom he said was a member of both West Lambeth Health
Authority and the Labour party. He quoted Mr Rowden as offering backing for
the changes in resource allocation and dismissing Labour's support for the
outgoing system as 'spurious.'
'Decisions before were arrived at by those that screamed loudest,' Mr Major
quoted the letter as saying.
Labour believes that, with the two parties level pegging in the national
opinion polls, concern about the impact of the changes could prove a crucial
factor in the coming general election.
