authority to negotiate a North American Free Trade agreement. Until
yesterday, the administration was considered likely to win approval from the
Senate, but the result in the House was too close to predict.
Mr Gephardt's support was accompanied by an attack on the Reagan and Bush
administrations for 'their failure to recognise the world as it is, instead
of how their ideologies say it should be.'
He insisted the House would renegotiate Nafta if it did not protect US jobs,
Mexican workers and the environment.
