<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 91 / World Stock Markets (Europe): Optimism about inflation
boosts Madrid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Markets Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SPANISH market broke out of its narrow trading range of the previous few
days, with a gain of 1.1 per cent in moderate trading. Most bourses were
closed yesterday for Ascension Day, writes Our Markets Staff.
MADRID firmed in response to rises on Wall Street and on hopes that next
week's inflation figure would show only a small rise. The general index
gained 3.0 to 282.55 in turnover of Pta13bn, up from Pta11bn.
A rumour that Banesto was looking to sell a stake in Petromed, its oil arm,
to BP at about Pta9,000 a share lifted Petromed Pta180 to Pta7,830. Cepsa, a
rival oil company, gained Pta50 to Pta2,240 in heavy volume of 232,291
shares.
The banking, oil and construction sectors were strong. Popular added Pta250
to Pta11,150 and Banesto gained Pta65 to Pta3,725.
MILAN closed little changed in technical trading before the end of the
trading month on May 15. The Comit index eased 0.5 to 574.38 in volume
estimated at less than Wednesday's meagre L109bn.
Pirelli Spa was one of the few big movers, rising L50 or 3 per cent to
L1,675 on news that the board of Continental, the German tyremaker, was
meeting at short notice to discuss possible co-operation with the Italian
company.
Alleanza, Generali's life insurance unit, also rose 3 per cent or L1,600 to
L53,100 after reporting a 26.7 per cent rise in 1990 net profit to L131.2bn
as well as a scrip issue.
HELSINKI rose 0.9 per cent with two large transactions dominating otherwise
quiet trading. Kesko, the wholesaler, gained FM0.50 to FM40 with 222,300
shares traded, while Interbank B shares slipped FM0.10 to FM12.90 on 148,000
shares. The Hex index added 10.09 to 1,089.62 as turnover eased to FM24m
from FM44.5m.
ATHENS's general index fell 34.53 or 3.1 per cent to 1,063.70, while the
banking index lost 61.48 or 4.9 per cent to 1,205.24. ISTANBUL's 75-share
index fell 86.89 or 2.3 per cent to 3,608.01.
Johannesburg was closed yesterday.
