</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UNITED Engineers, the Malaysian cement, construction and engineering group,
yesterday unveiled strong first-quarter results. The company lifted pre-tax
profits for the first quarter by 35 per cent to MDollars 35m (USDollars
12.6m) from MDollars 24m during the same period last year.
Turnover advanced to MDollars 99m, up from MDollars 88m previously, while
quarterly net profit rose 17 per cent to MDollars 20m to give earnings of
4.4 Malaysian cents a share, compared with 3.7 cents earlier.
Other companies within the group, Time Engineering, Cement Industries (Cima)
and Kinta Kellas, all reported a surge in pre-tax profit during the same
period.
Both Time and Kinta Kellas reversed their previous operating losses for
gains of MDollars 0.3m and MDollars 8m, respectively, on MDollars 44m and
MDollars 14m in turnover. At Cima, operating profit rose 41 per cent to
MDollars 8m on sales of MDollars 37m.
Net profits, which soared by 73 per cent and more among the three companies,
were MDollars 6m for Time, MDollars 5m for Kinta Kellas, and MDollars 11m
for Cima.
