FT  10 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Decline goes on at MMT Computing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KATRINA LOWE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A FURTHER downturn at MMT Computing in the six months to February 28 saw
taxable profits decline 38 per cent from Pounds 1.01m to Pounds 626,000.
This followed the previous full-year result of Pounds 1.87m, a fall of 13
per cent, writes Katrina Lowe.
The USM-quoted computer systems consultancy described the period as the most
difficult it had ever encountered. It had been forced to make redundancies
but the figure was less than 10.
It was still burdened with two leases on unused space at its previous
premises. The link with French computer group Axime, holder of a 20 per cent
stake in MMT, had produced no work. That situation had not changed in the
current half.
Of the two young subsidiaries, MMT Computing (AS) made its first
contribution 'at a very respectable level' but MMT Computing (Training)
incurred a loss; it looked likely, however, to report a profit for the
second half.
On prospects for the full year, Mr Mike Tilbrook, chairman, said: 'Analysts
have forecast profits of about Pounds 1.2m and the company has a history of
beating these forecasts.'
The interim dividend is maintained at 1p on earnings per share of 3.4p
(5.7p).
